<script type="text/javascript" src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js">// <![CDATA[</p>
<p>// ]]&gt;</script></div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<div id="attachment_7443" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 130px">
	<a href="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Samsung-Transform-Ultra-fs-1-test.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-7443 " title="Once Exclusive, Samsung Transform Ultra Goes To Sprint" src="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Samsung-Transform-Ultra-fs-1-test.jpg" alt="Once Exclusive, Samsung Transform Ultra Goes To Sprint" width="130" height="196" /></a>
	<p class="wp-caption-text">Once Exclusive, Samsung Transform Ultra Goes To Sprint - Image from Sprint</p>
</div>
<p>Samsung has now brought the <strong>Transform Ultra</strong>, an Android smartphone to Sprint. The smartphone which was an exclusive to Boost Mobile comes to Sprint stores . The Transform will probably sell for less under Sprint than at Boost Mobile.</p>
<p>The Transform Ultra from Samsung is powered by a 1GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon CPU and runs on Android 2.3 or Gingerbread. A 3.5-inch HVGA touchscreen and a slide-out full QWERTY keyboard complement the look.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Two cameras, a 3MP rear-facing and a VGA front-facing camera, will allow the user the ability to chat by video as well as take incredible still images and video. The Transform Ultra will be one of many smartphones from the carrier to feature the Sprint ID pack and will be able to download other packs as they become available.</p>
<p>The Transform Ultra will be able to connect via Wi-Fi or Bluetooth as well as the carriers network. The smartphone has GPS capability and it supports voice activated dialing. For more details on the Samsung Transform Ultra and the available network plans at Sprint <a href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.sprint.com%2Fnews%2Fsamsung-transform-ultra-fact-sheet.htm&sref=rss" rel="nofollow">click here</a>. According to this <a href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Freviews.cnet.com%2F8301-19736_7-20124675-251%2Fsamsung-transform-ultra-headed-to-sprint%2F&sref=rss" rel="nofollow">article</a> the Transform Ultra should be out now at Radio Shack and coming in November to Sprint stores..</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
