      <title>A New HTC Thunderbolt Update Is Leaked</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/GulfstreamNews/~3/Cb7uO1n9ZR0/</link>
      <comments>http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/a-new-htc-thunderbolt-update-is-leaked/7429/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 24 Oct 2011 15:48:55 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>SRETank</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Featured News]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[HTC]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[HTC ThunderBolt]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[leaked software fix]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[unofficial software update]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/?p=7429</guid>
      <description>// Yet another update has appeared for the HTC ThunderBolt, the &amp;#8216;leaked&amp;#8217; update is minor and the user will have to manually update their smartphone. However, this update may fixed the issues caused by the original update. This marks yet another chapter in the life of Thunderbolt users. The leaked update version number is 2.11.605.5 [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/gulfstream-news/Gulfstream_News-A_New_HTC_Thunderbolt_Update_Is_Leaked.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><div style="float: left; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 10px;"><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[
   google_ad_client = "pub-1450538712102813"; /* 300x250, created 4/26/11 */ google_ad_slot = "5911278597"; google_ad_width = 300; google_ad_height = 250;
// ]]&gt;</script><br />
<script src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js" type="text/javascript">
</script></div>
<p>Yet another update has appeared for the<strong> HTC ThunderBolt, </strong>the &#8216;leaked&#8217; update is minor and the user will have to manually update their smartphone. However, this update may fixed the issues caused by the original update. This marks yet another chapter in the life of Thunderbolt users.</p>
<div class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 130px">
	<a href="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/HTC-thunderbolt-amazon-sm-test.jpg"><img class="    " title="A New HTC Thunderbolt Update Is Leaked" src="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/HTC-thunderbolt-amazon-sm-test.jpg" alt="A New HTC Thunderbolt Update Is Leaked" width="130" height="184" /></a>
	<p class="wp-caption-text">Click on the image for a Deal on the ThunderBolt - A New HTC Thunderbolt Update Is Leaked</p>
</div>
<p>The leaked update version number is 2.11.605.5 and according to<a href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.androidpolice.com%2F2011%2F10%2F20%2Fexclusive-gingerbread-build-2-11-605-5-for-the-htc-thunderbolt-fixes-several-issues-from-the-previous-leak%2F&sref=rss"> this article</a>, fixes issues from the official OS update. As stated before the user will have to manually update their ThunderBolt. If the user is not comfortable with the instructions laid out in the article they will have to wait on the official update which may come at some futue date.</p>
<p>The Thunderbolt from HTC had received the Android 2.3  update (from Verizon Wireless) that  added a new Download Manager, it brought App and Power Management Details. The update also brought  improvements for data connectivity and SMS messages will be sent to correct recipient.For  more information on fixes and improvements <a href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.verizonwireless.com%2Fpdf%2Fsystem_update%2Fthunderbolt.pdf&sref=rss">click here</a>.</p>
<p>Packing a  1GHz Snapdragon  processor and running on Android  2.2, the ThunderBolt seems a  little big  at first. The 4.3-inch (WVGA) touch display only adds to already enjoyable    features. The handset also has a kickstand as part of its backing that    hides a Dolby SRS speaker. Not only will the user experience 4G LTE   speed (in areas where it is available), they will have access to social   networking sites such as Facebook, Twitter, and Flickr. With technology   becoming more and more mobile, who needs an extra and seperate GPS   device when the ThunderBolt already has Onboard GPS. Google apps such as   Google Maps provide turn-by-turn navigation with street an satellite views.</p>
<p><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[
         google_ad_client = "pub-1450538712102813"; /* 468x15, created 5/6/11 */ google_ad_slot = "5130440806"; google_ad_width = 468; google_ad_height = 15;
// ]]&gt;</script></p>
<p><script src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js" type="text/javascript">
</script></p>
<p>An  8GB memory, with the ability to upgrade to 32GB via microSD slot,  will  help the ThunderBolt 4G by HTC to blaze through using the 1.3MP   front-facing camera for video chat. The memory will allow the 8MP camera   with dual LED flash and autofocus shoot stills and shoot 720p HD  video.</p>
<p>With the accompanying Google software users will not have to worry   about excessive finger tapping on Google apps, one-touch will allow   faster access to Google Mobile apps. The lower price on Wirefly as compared to Verizon&#8217;s price  makes this decision a no-brainer for  people thinking about purchasing the HTC ThunderBolt 4G<img src="https://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=onthewebnow-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" border="0" alt="" width="1" height="1" />. <a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.kqzyfj.com%2Fclick-5414688-10753828&sref=rss">Click here for a deal on the ThunderBolt</a>!</p>
