<div id="attachment_6949" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 118px">
	<a href="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Sprint-epic_touch_4g-angle-fs.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-6949  " title="Best Display On A Dual-Core SmartPhone? - Samsung Galaxy Epic 4G Touch" src="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/Sprint-epic_touch_4g-angle-fs.jpg" alt="Best Display On A Dual-Core SmartPhone?" width="118" height="300" /></a>
	<p class="wp-caption-text">Best Display On A Dual-Core SmartPhone?</p>
</div>
<p>An eWeek article recently stated that the author thought the Samsung Epic 4G Touch has the best display of the current crop of dual-core smartphones. The mobile device which is a variant of the Samsung Galaxy S II that had first appeared globally before making its American debut. The mobile device currently sells for under $200 from Sprint (with agreement), features a new dual -core CPU and Super AMOLED Plus technology.</p>
<p>The Epic 4G Touch from Samsung is powered by a 1.2GHz dual-core Samsung Exynos processor and will be running on Android 2.3 &#8216;Gingerbread&#8217;. The mobile device will be a dual mode 3G/4G capable phone and will also support up to 8 Wi-Fi capable devices. Users will have an ultra-thin mobile gadget with a 4.52-inch touchscreen.</p>
<p>The Epic 4G Touch will be ready for use by the business professional through the use of Enterprise level functions. The consumer will be able to access entertainment type features such as Samsung&#8217;s Media and Social  Hubs. The user will have access to the TouchWiz UI and a task Manager which will allow the smartphone owner the ability to manage application resources.</p>
<p>The smartphone was launched in September and. the mobile device costs around $200 &#8211; excluding any fees &#8211; with a 2 year agreement. The features listed may or may not be the same at the time of launch.  <a href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB005LHN47S%2Fref%3Das_li_ss_tl%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Btag%3Donthewebnow-20%26amp%3BlinkCode%3Das2%26amp%3Bcamp%3D217145%26amp%3Bcreative%3D399373%26amp%3BcreativeASIN%3DB005LHN47S&sref=rss">Click here to purchase the Samsung Epic Touch 4G</a><img style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=onthewebnow-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B005LHN47S&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399373" border="0" alt="" width="1" height="1" />. Does it have the best dual-core smartphone display?<a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fmobile.eweek.com%2Fc%2Fa%2FMobile-and-Wireless%2FSamsung-Epic-4G-Touch-Sports-Best-Display-with-Dualcore-Power-636022%2F&sref=rss"> Click here for the article</a>.</p>
