<p>T-Mobile has put up a sign-up page on their site for email notifications for the T-Mobile SpringBoard with Google tablet computer. The listing shows that the tablet will have a 7-inch HD touch display and will come preloaded with Netflix and Blockbuster apps. A release put out by the carrier says that it will offer premium service to the user that won&#8217;t break the bank.</p>
<p>The SpringBoard for T-Mobile by Huawei will give its user access to the 4G network. The tablet is powered by  1.2 GHz dual-core mobile CPU and will run on Android 3.2 or &#8216;Honeycomb&#8217;. The tablet will come pre-loaded with software to entertain family and friends at home or on the go.</p>
<p>The SpringBoard will have both front facing (a 1.3MP) and rear facing (5MP &#8211; with video recording) digital cameras perfect for shooting still images or 720p HD video. These creations can be displayed on the 7-inch HD multi-touch display. The tablet will have such software pre-loaded as BlockBuster on Demand, Netflix and T-Mobile TV. The very portable device will also have such software as Slacker Radio and TeleNav GPS Navigator.</p>
<p>The SpringBoard tablet be available in time for the holidays and no price is available as yet. <a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fmobile-broadband.t-mobile.com%2Ftablets%2Fspringboard&sref=rss">Click here</a> for the sign-up page. <a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.t-mobile.com%2Farticles%2F4G-Tablet-Portfolio-Advances&sref=rss">Click here</a> for more details on the tablet. Any of these details may change prior to launch.</p>
