      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/?p=7307</guid>
      <description>// Users of the Motorola Droid X2 can now feel better about Gingerbread! The new update from Verizon fixes bugs and addresses issues with the previous Android 2.3 OS or &amp;#8216;Gingerbread&amp;#8217; update. Click here for more details on the improvements for the Droid X2. The new update can now be downloaded by manually by the [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/gulfstream-news/Gulfstream_News-Motorola_Droid_X2__Another_Update_Better_Gingerbread.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p></p><div style="float: left; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 10px;"><script type="text/javascript">// <![CDATA[
    google_ad_client = "pub-1450538712102813"; /* 300x250, created 4/26/11 */ google_ad_slot = "5911278597"; google_ad_width = 300; google_ad_height = 250;
// ]]&gt;</script><br />
<script src="http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js" type="text/javascript">
</script></div>
<div id="attachment_6395" class="wp-caption alignright" style="width: 130px">
	<a href="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/amazon-Moto-Droid-x2-test.jpg"><img class="size-full wp-image-6395  " title="Motorola Droid X2 - Another Update, Better Gingerbread" src="http://gulfstreamcleaning.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/08/amazon-Moto-Droid-x2-test.jpg" alt="Motorola Droid X2 - Another Update, Better Gingerbread" width="130" height="250" /></a>
	<p class="wp-caption-text">Click on the image for more info on - Motorola Droid X2 - Another Update, Better Gingerbread</p>
</div>
<p>Users of the <strong>Motorola Droid X2</strong> can now feel better about Gingerbread! The new update from Verizon fixes bugs and addresses issues with the previous Android 2.3 OS or  &#8216;Gingerbread&#8217; update. <a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.verizonwireless.com%2Fpdf%2Fsystem_update%2Fdroidx2.pdf&sref=rss">Click here</a> for more details on the improvements for the Droid X2. The new update can now be downloaded by manually by the user. <a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsupport.verizonwireless.com%2Fpdf%2Fsystem_update%2Fdroidx2_instructions.pdf&sref=rss">Click here</a> for the update.</p>
<p>Among the improvements are: the keyboard will remain visible when the user is putting in text, it will no longer experience lock-ups or resets when using the keyboard, and other fixes that have plagued users of this smartphone.</p>
<p>The Motorola Droid X2 is powered by a  1GHz Nvidia Tegra 2 dual-core chip. it will of course feature Mobile  Hotspot capability allowing the user to share a 3G connection with up to  five Wi-Fi capable gadgets. The business professional will be able to  take advantage of it enterprise-ready security and business- grade  policy features. A touch screen at 4.3 inches scratch-resistant (Gorilla  Glass) and anti-reflective qHD display, will easily display a full  QWERTY keyboard when needed. With a resolution that may be 540&#215;960 with  the ever ready acceleromter for UI auto-rotate.</p>
<p>Never miss a precious moment using the 8MP camera with continuous  autofocus and dual-LED flash for stunning HD (30fps) video capture. Use  the new Gallery app to view, geo tag and post photos on sites like  Flickr and Facebook, all from one place. All with the help of 512MB RAM,  and 8GB of internal memory. A feature called Mirror Mode allows you to  view and share your photos, videos and downloaded movies on a larger TV  via HDMI output.</p>
<p>Support for Google Mobile Services, including Gmail, YouTube, Google  Talk, Search, and Maps as well as other Android applications that are  available from the Android Market will be available too. <a rel="nofollow" href="http://redirectingat.com?id=10040X685899&xs=1&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fgp%2Fproduct%2FB0050KAO5Q%2Fref%3Das_li_qf_sp_asin_tl%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Btag%3Donthewebnow-20%26amp%3BlinkCode%3Das2%26amp%3Bcamp%3D217145%26amp%3Bcreative%3D399373%26amp%3BcreativeASIN%3DB0050KAO5Q&sref=rss">Click here to buy the Motorola DROID X2 Android Phone (Verizon Wireless) from Amazon Wireless</a><img style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=onthewebnow-20&amp;l=as2&amp;o=1&amp;a=B0050KAO5Q&amp;camp=217145&amp;creative=399373" border="0" alt="" width="1" height="1" />.</p>
<p>The Motorola Droid X2 is now available for a penny (excluding taxes and  additional fees) from Amazon with a two-year agreement. This smartphone is given  carrier service via Verizon.</p>
